		<!-- modal -->
		<div id="openModalSpace" class="modalDialog">
				<div>
					<a href="#close" title="Close" class="close">X</a>
					<div class="large_image">
						<img src="asset
s/img/sibling_rivalry.png" alt="Space Multiplication">
					</div>
					<div class="content">
						<h2 class="title">Space Multiplication: 350%</h2>
						<p>By using the surface of the Pyramid-like shape, we are able to stack up a lot more plants one above the other, for upto 5 layers. This leads to a space gain of 350%!<br><br>The inside of the pyramid is filled with soil mix. It is possible to create inter-cropping patterns - a <em>Guild</em>, or <em>Mandala</em> of your own making!<br><br>To conventionally grow 42 plants in 2D rows requires over 42 square feet. But the Pyramid Garden is able to achieve that in just 6 square feet!<br><br>This vertical stacking up also has many other advantages such as better sharing of water across slope of pyramid.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
		</div>
		<!-- end modal -->
		<!-- modal -->
		<div id="openModalAdvantages" class="modalDialog">
				<div>
					<a href="#close" title="Close" class="close">X</a>
					<div class="large_image">
						<img src="assets/img/modmulch.gif" alt="Modular Mulch">
					</div>
					<div class="content">
						<h2 class="title">Space, Water & Effort saving</h2>
						<p>The Modular Mulch is an innovation that provides continuous mulching as well as periodic adding of soil microbes. The Mulch comes filled with soil microbes (ghanajeevamrutham) as well as hay of organic paddy and dry leaves of organic trees such as Neem, Noni, Pongamia, Teak, and so on. It is designed to decompose and become part of the topsoil. It has to be replaced once in every 2-3 months and it can be done without disturbing any of your existing plants on the pyramid! <br><br>The Modular Mulch on the Pyramid Garden prevents growth of weeds, holds the soil in tact without erosion, keeps the soil cooler, reduces moisture evaporation and thus water intake, keeps optimal air circulation, and in general makes it possible to do <em>No Till farming</em> even in your terrace!<br><br>What more? Every replacement of the modular mulch helps rural livelihoods and the revival of the desi cow from whose dung the microbe culture is synthesized.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
		</div>
		<!-- end modal -->
		<!-- modal -->
		<div id="openModalComposting" class="modalDialog">
				<div>
					<a href="#close" title="Close" class="close">X</a>
					<div class="large_image">
						<img src="assets/img/schematic-composting.png" alt="Integrated Composting">
					</div>
					<div class="content">
						<h2 class="title">Integrated Composting</h2>
						<p>The Pyramid Garden comes also with a Composting facility. Since the soil mix we recommend involves desi cow dung farm yard manure, the soil mix will contain the eggs of earth worms. These earth worms are not only beneficial to plants, but can also be used for turning our waste into vermicompost! At the center of the pyramid is a pipe with holes all around it. The earth worms can easily move in and out of the composting unit. The wet waste is to be added from the top and after about 2-3 months of proper composting, the compost can be taken out from bottom.<br><br>We estimate that at the peak of earth worm population, this system should be able to process 1-2 KG of wet waste every day<br><br>The vermicasts are cast under the mulch layer as per the natural tendency of the earth worms and this is where the plants' roots are.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
		</div>
